				\begin{document}$$G_{{{\text{NH}}_{2} - {\text{NH}}_{3} }}$$\end{document}). The detailed threshold values are listed in Fig. 4b, and these steps theoretically require a large energy input and are usually the PLS of the NRR (Table 1). A total of 97 ASCs were selected in the first step (Fig. 4c) because they strongly interact with N2 and can hydrogenate N2 to N2H with high performance (red region), while 10 highly active ASCs were selected in the second step (Fig. 4d). Among the ASCs, W1C3 exhibited the best NRR performance with a UL value of − 0.25 V through the enzymatic mechanism (Fig. 4e). This benchmarking work provided an example of high-throughput DFT calculations that accelerated the discovery of NRR ASCs.Fig. 4
